{"id": 232036016, "title": "Man who shed almost 10 stone shares weight loss secret - and anyone can do it", "text": "A man whose size left him unable to buy clothes from the high street has shared his secret to shedding almost 10 stone. Jack Self, from Bolton, tipped the scales at 24st 10.5lbs when he decided to change his lifestyle habits for good in March 2023. The 23-year-old had struggled with his weight for years and felt limited in his movement and what exercise he could do. READ MORE: Mum who shed almost four and a half stone shares secret key to weight loss success The student decided to sign up to his local Slimming World group in the Daisy Hill area having seen the success his partner had with the group. Initially hesitant to sign up due to a lack of other young men in the club, Jack watched as the weight dropped off \u2013 so far losing an incredible 9.5st. \u201cMy confidence has grown massively,\u201d he told the Manchester Evening News. \u201cI am now four sizes smaller and the issue of not finding clothes that fit is no longer. \u201cMy mobility and physical limitations are also a thing of the past as I am now very active and enjoy fitness. \u201cMy health feels like it has greatly improved, and day-by-day I feel as if 14 months ago was a lot longer.\u201d Jack, who has a target weight of 13.5st, has since gained 24,000 followers on TikTok thanks to sharing meal ideas on his account, fatboyslimmer00. The Manchester United fan credits his weight loss success to following the Slimming World diet plan, calorie counting, walking and the occasional run. But he says one tip is key \u2013 never cut out anything you enjoy eating. \u201cI have one night a week where I enjoy myself and have something I wouldn\u2019t have for the rest of the week,\u201d he added.\u201d \u201cLooking back, I really did not notice how big I had actually got and how much weight I\u2019d gained. \u201cI would say I\u2019ve come a long way in my 14-month journey and I\u2019m beginning to feel proud of what I\u2019ve achieved so far.\u201d Catherine Cleary, the group's consultant, said: \u201cJack\u2019s dedication has undoubtedly brought a new dynamic to the evening session, which now boasts three more men inspired by his progress. \u201cEmbracing Slimming World's unique Body Magic plan, Jack has developed a newfound love for running, regularly setting and breaking personal records. \u201cHis passion for healthy living extends to the kitchen, where he has become a TikTok sensation under the handle Fatboyslimmer00, sharing his culinary creations with a growing audience. \u201cJack's journey is a testament to the transformative power of determination and support. \u201cHis story is not just about weight loss, but about gaining a healthier, more vibrant life. He looks fantastic and serves as an inspiration to all.\u201d", "summary": "Jack Self, from Bolton, tipped the scales at more than 24 stone. Then he embraced a diet and exercise plan he's been able to stick to - by giving himself one night off", "url": "https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/man-who-shed-almost-10-29289767", "image": "https://i2-prod.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/incoming/article29297797.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Untitled-design-2.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 15:24:33", "author": "Paige Oldfield", "authors": ["Paige Oldfield"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.439}